1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:32,980
= Episode 32 =

20
00:01:45,180 --> 00:01:49,540
Confucius said,
benevolence is from restraint and courtesy.

21
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:52,340
Once there is restraint and courtesy,

22
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:55,060
= Shi Jie, courtesy name Shoudao =
there will be benevolence in the world.

23
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:59,460
Confucius said,
benevolence is from restraint and courtesy.

24
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:01,580
Once there is restraint and courtesy...

25
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:04,460
So much for the reading today.

26
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,900
We’ll come to the type of writing.

27
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,860
Today, I’m teaching you how to write an ode.

28
00:02:11,420 --> 00:02:13,980
I’ll write one regarding current politics.

29
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:15,700
Come over.

30
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:16,980
All of you.

31
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:39,460
= 1043 A.D. =

32
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:42,220
Mr. Shi is praising my father,

33
00:02:42,220 --> 00:02:42,900
isn’t he?

34
00:02:43,660 --> 00:02:45,340
Since His Majesty is involved,

35
00:02:45,820 --> 00:02:47,460
it will be something commendatory.

36
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,460
Sister, go.

37
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,340
Go get the ink ready.

38
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,380
I’m going to copy this.

39
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:03,660
As a gifted scholar,

40
00:03:04,580 --> 00:03:05,740
Ouyang Xiu does nothing good.

41
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:09,420
What a nuisance!

42
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,420
At Flower Festival,

43
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:15,660
I got to know Wang Gongchen’s wife Madam Xue.

44
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:17,380
I asked her

45
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:19,300
why she didn’t associate with

46
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:21,020
her own sister Mrs. Ouyang.

47
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:24,100
She told me how Mrs. Ouyang

48
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:26,020
looked down on her

49
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,420
for she was the daughter of a concubine

50
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,220
and how her brother-in-law Ouyang Xiu

51
00:03:31,060 --> 00:03:31,820
humiliated her husband in public

52
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:33,180
several times.

53
00:03:35,180 --> 00:03:37,020
Ouyang Xiu is so mean.

54
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:39,340
He’ll get his retribution sooner or later.

55
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,140
Oh, madam.

56
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:45,380
Lately,

57
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,620
you’ve had a better social life.

58
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,260
You get on well with your uncle.

59
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:51,540
Through him,

60
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,500
you make friends
with more female members of officials.

61
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:57,300
Even including wives of Chen Zhizhong, Wen Yanbo

62
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:59,340
and Wang Gongchen.

63
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:02,340
The Empress

64
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:05,940
will no longer dictate all affairs alone.

65
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:11,180
Your Highness.

66
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:15,540
Huirou.

67
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:16,420
Your Highness.

68
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,260
Bring the dessert and dried apricots

69
00:04:18,260 --> 00:04:19,180
made this noon.

70
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:21,220
The school was just over.

71
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:22,420
Why are you in such a hurry?

72
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:24,300
Look, your hair is in a mess.

73
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:27,060
Your Highness.

74
00:04:29,020 --> 00:04:30,900
Today,

75
00:04:30,940 --> 00:04:32,180
Mr. Shi taught us how to write an ode.

76
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:33,460
Then he wrote this,

77
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,060
praising father for being wise, taking advice,

78
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,780
promoting good officials instead of villains.

79
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:40,940
In recent months,

80
00:04:41,220 --> 00:04:42,460
Yan Shu became the prime minister.

81
00:04:42,580 --> 00:04:44,180
Fan Zhongyan, Han Qi and Fu Bi

82
00:04:44,180 --> 00:04:45,060
were promoted.

83
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:47,300
The imperial court has been thriving.

84
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,060
Mr. Shi was so happy

85
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:50,460
that he praised that in class.

86
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:52,620
Mr. Shi

87
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,140
greatly praised Mr. Fan Zhongyan

88
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:56,460
and Mr. Han Qi.

89
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:59,420
He then reprimanded Xia Song as a villain.

90
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:02,100
Your Highness, look. Here.

91
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:05,380
Using wise men is like pulling up the weeds.

92
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:07,740
Dismissing villains is like cutting chicken feet.

93
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:10,660
Mr. Shi didn’t say that clearly in the text.

94
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:13,300
But it can be seen in the preface.

95
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:14,900
Your Highness, look.

96
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:16,740
Here. This sentence.

97
00:05:17,140 --> 00:05:19,820
“Dismissing Song as Chief Executive”.

98
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:22,060
It says Xia Song is no longer the Chief Executive,

99
00:05:23,180 --> 00:05:25,380
which corresponds to dismissing the villain
in the text.

100
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:27,300
Your Highness, am I right?

101
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,740
In the preface, Mr. Shi also says,

102
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:32,380
father promoted Fan Zhongyan and Han Qi.

103
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:34,220
He removed Xia Song

104
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:35,260
from Chief Executive

105
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,980
with memorials of many good officials.

106
00:05:37,660 --> 00:05:39,340
This is a great thing

107
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:40,300
that everyone in this world

108
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:42,020
would like to see.

109
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:51,060
Your Highness, is there anything wrong?

110
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:54,700
Nothing wrong.

111
00:05:56,380 --> 00:06:00,020
But calling Xia Song a villain leaves no room

112
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:02,980
and will make them enemies.

113
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:06,180
Your Highness, why must we leave room

114
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:07,700
for villains?

115
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,020
In politics,

116
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:14,020
there is no absolute goodness or badness.

117
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,820
Anyway, I know.

118
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:17,180
Xia Song gets on well with

119
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:19,140
Aunt Jia who works for Madam Zhang.

120
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:21,340
He can’t be a good man.

121
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:23,500
So, letting him leave the Capital

122
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,860
and no longer advise father

123
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:26,260
will be a good thing, too.

124
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,580
Everyone in this world

125
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:29,500
would like to see that.

126
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,140
Huirou.

127
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:33,380
Don’t talk nonsense.

128
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:36,740
Your Highness, if you insist that

129
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:38,340
Madam Zhang is a good woman

130
00:06:38,340 --> 00:06:39,300
and a good concubine,

131
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:40,900
I don’t dare to refute that.

132
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:43,060
I don’t dare to argue with you.

133
00:06:43,660 --> 00:06:44,420
But...

134
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,900
if you force me

135
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,900
to think or say in the same way,

136
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,540
I can’t do that.

137
00:06:49,820 --> 00:06:51,220
I hate her.

138
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:54,620
Huirou.

139
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:57,420
I just want you to know.

140
00:06:57,980 --> 00:06:59,140
When you like someone

141
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:00,860
or especially when you hate someone,

142
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:02,460
you can’t put all your feelings

143
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:03,420
on your face.

144
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,540
It’s not good for others,

145
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:07,260
and even for you.

146
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,220
I’m not scared of her.

147
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:09,980
You’re not scared of her.

148
00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:11,620
Why?

149
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:13,980
She’s not scared of you.

150
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,460
And why?

151
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:19,580
Your Highness, I’m unlike her.

152
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:21,660
In this matter,

153
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:24,180
you aren’t scared of each other
and you dare to compete

154
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:26,420
only because of the same thing.

155
00:07:27,340 --> 00:07:29,020
Because your father loves you

156
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,580
and cares for you.

157
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:39,540
Huirou.

158
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:42,300
You’re not scared of her.

159
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,260
But someone else will be.

160
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:47,220
You’re not scared.

161
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:50,460
But your mother is very scared.

162
00:07:51,660 --> 00:07:53,100
She is a gentle woman,

163
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:54,620
who doesn’t compete with anyone.

164
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:57,340
But now, she’s afraid that she isn’t

165
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:59,420
strong or scheming enough to defend you.

166
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,780
You must be thirsty.

167
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:11,940
Bring it here.

168
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,860
I’ve prepared you

169
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:21,540
the plum dessert and dried apricots.

170
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:31,420
Cuisines made by Imperial Cooks

171
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,460
are delicious.

172
00:08:33,140 --> 00:08:34,300
But they remain the same

173
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,380
in the past decades.

174
00:08:37,020 --> 00:08:38,260
When I read printed books today,

175
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,580
I came up with an idea.

176
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:44,580
If one day,

177
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:46,260
someone compiles a book of the cuisines

178
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:48,060
from local restaurants

179
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,340
and prints thousands of copies,

180
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:52,580
everyone from the cities to the borders

181
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:54,940
will be able to enjoy the cuisines

182
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:56,260
from the Capital.

183
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:58,260
Your Majesty,

184
00:08:58,340 --> 00:08:59,540
if you didn’t bring it up,

185
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:01,060
we wouldn’t have known

186
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:02,300
you even thought of cuisines in the Capital

187
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:04,460
when you talked with ministers about politics.

188
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:09,540
Food is the first necessity of the people.

189
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:10,860
If I care for my people,

190
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,020
I will always think of food.

191
00:09:12,780 --> 00:09:13,420
Your Majesty.

192
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:15,980
Her Highness asks to see you.

193
00:09:19,060 --> 00:09:20,140
Get her in.

194
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:23,620
Go get her the chopsticks.

195
00:09:23,780 --> 00:09:25,780
And fetch the wine I’ve collected.

196
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:26,940
Aye.

197
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:31,700
= Xia Mansion =

198
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,620
My lord. My lord.

199
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:36,100
It’ll be a long trip.

200
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:38,940
With a few broken carts and weak horses,

201
00:09:38,940 --> 00:09:40,980
I can’t take all of you with me.

202
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:43,980
My lord, but we...

203
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:46,620
I’m banished from the Capital.

204
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:48,540
If I take so much treasure

205
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:49,620
and so many beauties,

206
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:51,300
before I leave the Capital,

207
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:53,820
Ouyang Xiu will have submitted

208
00:09:53,820 --> 00:09:55,500
countless proposals to impeach me.

209
00:09:55,940 --> 00:09:57,540
By then,

210
00:09:57,980 --> 00:09:59,780
I will not be dismissed or banished,

211
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:01,980
but be killed with property confiscated.

212
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:04,460
My lord, we...

213
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:05,540
I don’t think

214
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:08,300
you need to leave the Capital with me.

215
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,820
Some of you who stayed long with me

216
00:10:10,060 --> 00:10:11,900
can afford a house in western suburbs.

217
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:13,740
Those who stayed a bit shorter

218
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:15,580
also saved much money, didn’t you?

219
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:18,660
You’re young and beautiful.

220
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:20,660
Why don’t you find another man

221
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:22,020
or go back to the brothel?

222
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:26,260
- No, My lord... - No!

223
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:28,340
I’m going out for some business!

224
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:31,180
When I’m away,

225
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,500
think about it carefully.

226
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:34,860
Whoever wants to leave with me

227
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:36,660
shall only carry one piece of luggage.

228
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:39,340
Whoever wants to stay

229
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:40,620
can take away

230
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:41,780
whatever you want

231
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:43,820
from this mansion

232
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:45,300
that I haven’t packed.

233
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:47,700
My lord...

234
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,700
If you really want to repay me,

235
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:52,220
there is another way,

236
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:54,260
much better than

237
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,380
leaving the Capital and suffering with me.

238
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:57,460
What is it, My lord? Tell us.

239
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:58,340
Tell us.

240
00:10:58,820 --> 00:10:59,980
Just tell

241
00:11:00,180 --> 00:11:01,940
those girls in the brothel

242
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,860
that sing or tell stories

243
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:05,940
about who made me

244
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:08,340
in such trouble.

245
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:10,780
Those two guys!

246
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:13,740
Tell people about their stories.

247
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:17,380
And the personal affair of another man.

248
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:19,540
Who is he? Tell us.

249
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,540
- My lord. - Tell us.

250
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:23,660
The famous scholar Ouyang Xiu.

251
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:26,580
Ouyang Xiu?

252
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:28,700
Moveable-type printing.

253
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:31,340
Now few publishing houses

254
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:33,460
know it, learn it or use it.

255
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:34,860
But I think

256
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,780
if it can prevail someday,

257
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:40,660
the price of books will tumble.

258
00:11:41,460 --> 00:11:43,500
Crafts and diets.

259
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,700
Everything can be printed into books.

260
00:11:45,020 --> 00:11:46,500
Scholars can read.

261
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:48,300
Farmers can read, too.

262
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:50,740
In this way,

263
00:11:52,460 --> 00:11:56,180
people will learn principles and be enlightened.

264
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:05,460
Danshu.

265
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:12,860
I’ve got a lot of things to do.

266
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:24,380
Your Majesty.

267
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,060
I know.

268
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:35,380
You not only want to print more books,

269
00:12:36,180 --> 00:12:37,300
enlighten commoners,

270
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,540
compile medical classics,

271
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:43,180
and compile General Military Principles,

272
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:52,420
but also reduce officials
and improve their management.

273
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,340
All these years,

274
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:21,740
I’ve been trying to remove barriers

275
00:13:22,020 --> 00:13:24,900
for farming, business and all crafts.

276
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:28,540
In the past ten years,

277
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:34,100
wastelands and fields have been farmed.

278
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:39,940
Business and crafts have been developed, too.

279
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:43,020
The revenues have jumped.

280
00:13:43,580 --> 00:13:45,420
But all the revenues

281
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:48,620
are consumed by redundant officials.

282
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:53,500
I can tolerate that, though.

283
00:13:55,220 --> 00:13:57,140
But from Feng Shiyuan’s case,

284
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:01,180
I realize the officials’ management is too stale.

285
00:14:04,380 --> 00:14:06,860
It not only consumes the tax revenues,

286
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:10,460
but also harms social principles.

287
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:19,540
Danshu, I’m expecting.

288
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:24,860
But I’m also scared.

289
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:28,860
When officials’ management is reformed,

290
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:32,300
commoners can’t see the benefits

291
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:33,980
on the state or themselves.

292
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:38,780
But officials involved

293
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,580
will lose a lot.

294
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,060
Stop.

295
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:21,540
Hya.

296
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:23,780
Hya.

297
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:34,780
= Ode to Qingli Holiness =

298
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:58,820
Got everything hidden?

299
00:16:05,140 --> 00:16:06,380
I’m glad you helped.

300
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:10,420
I’ve given everything I have

301
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,340
to you.

302
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:20,620
Bihan is a sentimental woman.

303
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,300
I was wondering

304
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:25,860
how to tell her I wanted to come here.

305
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:28,420
She asked me first.

306
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:30,860
She asked me when you would leave

307
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:35,580
and told me to see you before you went.

308
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,180
Yes. Yes.

309
00:16:42,540 --> 00:16:44,300
His Majesty is more sentimental.

310
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,340
Since he already knew

311
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:49,940
what happened to us,

312
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:52,220
when you come and meet me,

313
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:54,300
even if he knows,

314
00:16:55,460 --> 00:16:57,220
he won’t blame you.

315
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,340
Maybe,

316
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:03,620
he’ll have a better impression of me.

317
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:13,580
Your wife is not only rude,

318
00:17:13,580 --> 00:17:15,300
she’s totally insane!

319
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:19,020
Look what she’s done to you!

320
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:22,100
You overestimate her.

321
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:23,900
She’s nobody,

322
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,580
but a cat’s paw.

323
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:29,020
Some officials are against me.

324
00:17:32,580 --> 00:17:33,420
Who do you mean?

325
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,340
Except me,

326
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:50,980
the rest in this ode

327
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:52,620
is against me.

328
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:57,500
What a useful ode!

329
00:17:58,180 --> 00:17:59,780
It gives me a list of names

330
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:03,300
so that I can cross them out one by one.

331
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:09,940
= Ouyang Xiu, Fan Zhongyan, Han Qi =

332
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,620
This time, I will make good use.

333
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:49,020
About Wang Gongchen,

334
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,740
Bihan is getting close

335
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:52,620
to his wife.

336
00:18:54,020 --> 00:18:54,980
Should I...

337
00:18:58,260 --> 00:19:00,460
You only need to

338
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:03,580
take good care of Zhang Bihan.

339
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:07,220
His Majesty is sentimental.

340
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:09,460
When he thinks

341
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:11,460
you truly care for Zhang Bihan,

342
00:19:14,060 --> 00:19:16,580
he won’t blame you for small problems.

343
00:19:18,860 --> 00:19:21,260
I’ve got a plan for Wang Gongchen.

344
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:23,540
You don’t need to bother.

345
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:33,100
Fine, then.

346
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:37,380
Have you got someone else

347
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:39,660
who works better

348
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,220
and now you don’t need me?

349
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:48,820
You’d better not

350
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:50,060
interfere with such business.

351
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,820
I’ll just bring it up

352
00:19:54,820 --> 00:19:56,620
what happened to

353
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:57,940
Wang Gongchen and Ouyang Xiu.

354
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:02,740
I’ve spent so much money raising the girls.

355
00:20:03,260 --> 00:20:04,820
They must be used, huh?

356
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:11,660
But you’re different.

357
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:14,940
I owe you what I can never repay.

358
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:20,100
How can I get you involved again?

359
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,580
Don’t say that.

360
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:27,900
You know,

361
00:20:29,060 --> 00:20:31,260
your wife gets insane, because...

362
00:20:34,220 --> 00:20:35,100
Don’t say that.

363
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:37,940
You don’t need to explain.

364
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,740
For himself, a man does everything.

365
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:46,300
You did that because you loved me, anyway.

366
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:11,260
It’s the ninth time

367
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:14,620
that Yuanhao asked to make peace.

368
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:20,340
Wang Yaochen commands the western front

369
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:21,580
with full defense

370
00:21:22,540 --> 00:21:24,020
Di Qing and the others are defending.

371
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:28,180
Yuanhao had small victories.

372
00:21:28,940 --> 00:21:30,420
But he can’t break through the line.

373
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:34,940
Last winter,

374
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,860
many of his people died.

375
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:39,740
Wang Yaochen said

376
00:21:41,420 --> 00:21:43,100
they didn’t attack

377
00:21:43,140 --> 00:21:44,900
as strongly as they did

378
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:46,260
years ago

379
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:47,660
and maybe we could make peace.

380
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:52,980
Di Qing said we could wait for another winter

381
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:54,380
and make peace next year.

382
00:21:58,020 --> 00:21:59,380
I supported Di Qing.

383
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:03,460
I supported him,

384
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:05,180
because I want

385
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:10,100
Yuanhao to abdicate himself

386
00:22:10,420 --> 00:22:12,340
and give allegiance to our nation.

387
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:16,900
You don’t dare to lose ancestral properties.

388
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:20,620
I understand, Your Majesty.

389
00:22:23,340 --> 00:22:24,700
Otherwise,

390
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:26,820
you...

391
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:33,380
you wouldn’t have sacrificed soldiers.

392
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,380
You must be tired.

393
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:46,740
Have some sleep.

394
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,940
I’ll be with you.

395
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:01,580
When I do something proud,

396
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:07,260
I’d like to tell you first

397
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:08,540
that I’ve done a good job.

398
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:13,500
When I fail,

399
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,140
I don’t want to see you

400
00:23:16,420 --> 00:23:17,820
in case you might know.

401
00:23:20,140 --> 00:23:22,260
But when I’m worried or scared,

402
00:23:24,540 --> 00:23:26,140
I always think of you.

403
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:34,060
Just like when I faced the Empress Dowager

404
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:39,660
at a young age.

405
00:24:06,060 --> 00:24:06,780
Master.

406
00:24:07,420 --> 00:24:09,660
Are we just going to wait and do nothing?

407
00:24:11,060 --> 00:24:12,060
Since His Majesty

408
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:13,140
said that to me,

409
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:14,620
I couldn’t even sleep well.

410
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:18,140
What else do you want to do then?

411
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:19,940
To rebel?

412
00:24:22,180 --> 00:24:24,340
Master, even if I kill myself,

413
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:26,340
I don’t dare to rebel.

414
00:24:28,020 --> 00:24:29,460
What do you want then?

415
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,820
Aunt Jia colluded with Xia Song

416
00:24:34,820 --> 00:24:35,900
to sell untaxed salt and girls.

417
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:36,980
The evidence

418
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,140
can get her in jail for years.

419
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:41,660
At least, she’ll be expelled.

420
00:24:42,820 --> 00:24:43,860
What does that help?

421
00:24:44,380 --> 00:24:45,460
If so,

422
00:24:45,980 --> 00:24:47,700
I wouldn’t have gotten her back.

423
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,340
Get up. No more kneeling.

424
00:24:57,420 --> 00:24:59,060
We should at least

425
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:01,500
stop her from making trouble again

426
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:02,780
and accumulate strength for you-know-who.

427
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:05,580
Liaozi.

428
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,140
What His Majesty said that day

429
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,380
is invaluable advice.

430
00:25:09,820 --> 00:25:11,140
As long as you remember it,

431
00:25:11,620 --> 00:25:12,620
you won’t be killed.

432
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,180
When you don’t make mistakes

433
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:18,780
or go against rules,

434
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:21,580
you’ll live what you’re living

435
00:25:21,740 --> 00:25:23,060
and do what you’re doing.

436
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:27,420
But...

437
00:25:27,540 --> 00:25:29,740
But our rivals force us to make mistakes.

438
00:25:30,620 --> 00:25:31,420
Just like me.

439
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:34,460
I’m forcing Madam Zhang.

440
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:37,340
We’ll see who takes actions first

441
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:38,700
to make mistakes

442
00:25:38,980 --> 00:25:40,700
or even rebel.

443
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:44,580
You should never hurry.

444
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:46,180
You need patience.

445
00:25:47,340 --> 00:25:48,900
You can’t

446
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:49,780
just expose the rival’s mistake

447
00:25:49,860 --> 00:25:50,820
in such a hurry

448
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:51,980
when you find it.

449
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:54,460
You’ll be correcting her.

450
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:05,660
= Hall of Happiness and Tranquility =

451
00:26:35,780 --> 00:26:37,220
Yesterday,

452
00:26:38,180 --> 00:26:39,460
I came here

453
00:26:39,660 --> 00:26:40,700
because I had something

454
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:41,980
to discuss with you.

455
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:43,460
What is it?

456
00:26:45,980 --> 00:26:47,940
Huirou is seven years old.

457
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:50,980
She’s turning a young girl.

458
00:26:52,740 --> 00:26:54,780
And she grew up in the palace,

459
00:26:55,300 --> 00:26:56,500
with extraordinary knowledge.

460
00:26:57,340 --> 00:26:59,380
She’s wiser than ordinary children.

461
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:01,540
I don’t think

462
00:27:02,180 --> 00:27:03,980
she should still

463
00:27:04,340 --> 00:27:06,340
take classes with young boys

464
00:27:08,100 --> 00:27:09,500
from the imperial family.

465
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:15,220
Someone flirted with her?

466
00:27:18,060 --> 00:27:19,220
Don’t be nervous, Your Majesty.

467
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:20,740
No one did that.

468
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:27,300
You must have a reason for that.

469
00:27:29,100 --> 00:27:31,820
Yesterday, Mr. Shi Jie

470
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:35,540
wrote an ode in class.

471
00:27:38,420 --> 00:27:41,860
He always writes beautifully, of course.

472
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:45,140
But in the ode,

473
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:46,540
he clearly praised you

474
00:27:47,020 --> 00:27:49,100
for using wise officials instead of villains.

475
00:27:50,380 --> 00:27:52,500
Shi Jie is a pedantic man.

476
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:56,220
When I am going to reform officials’ management,

477
00:27:57,420 --> 00:28:00,060
some people will certainly hate

478
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:02,380
Fan Zhongyan, Han Qi and Fu Bi.

479
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:06,340
But it’s not necessary to make people

480
00:28:06,340 --> 00:28:07,620
hate them at the very beginning.

481
00:28:09,380 --> 00:28:11,220
Such scholars and students

482
00:28:11,980 --> 00:28:13,660
express their feelings whenever inspired.

483
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:14,860
They can not be stopped.

484
00:28:15,980 --> 00:28:18,900
It brings advantages and disadvantages, anyway.

485
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:21,980
A teacher usually uses current politics

486
00:28:23,020 --> 00:28:24,700
when giving a class.

487
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:27,580
It’s very useful

488
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:29,180
for the boys of the imperial family.

489
00:28:30,820 --> 00:28:31,940
But Huirou...

490
00:28:32,820 --> 00:28:34,500
She’s your eldest daughter.

491
00:28:35,180 --> 00:28:36,700
She’s neither young nor old.

492
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:37,580
And she doesn’t understand everything.

493
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:40,460
It’s hard to reason with her.

494
00:28:41,580 --> 00:28:42,780
If one day,

495
00:28:43,220 --> 00:28:45,060
she misjudges current politics

496
00:28:45,660 --> 00:28:47,260
and someone hears her,

497
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:49,300
there’ll be trouble, I’m afraid.

498
00:28:53,460 --> 00:28:54,340
You’re right.

499
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:58,700
I should have thought of that.

500
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:02,300
If she didn’t come to me yesterday,

501
00:29:02,980 --> 00:29:04,220
I wouldn’t have thought of this, either.

502
00:29:05,740 --> 00:29:08,180
A princess doesn’t need to go
to the Imperial School.

503
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:09,980
But I think

504
00:29:10,620 --> 00:29:11,700
my princesses

505
00:29:11,860 --> 00:29:12,980
aren’t ordinary girls.

506
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:15,460
Even if they don’t need the knowledge,

507
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:20,020
they need the mind and temperament

508
00:29:20,740 --> 00:29:22,780
trained by famous teachers.

509
00:29:23,340 --> 00:29:24,220
Just like you.

510
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:27,260
You also went to Nanjing Academy

511
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:28,980
and took classes from Fan Zhongyan

512
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:31,420
with some boy classmates.

513
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:36,780
Pitiful.

514
00:29:38,220 --> 00:29:39,540
Not really.

515
00:29:44,260 --> 00:29:47,460
What does it help if a girl is like me?

516
00:29:48,820 --> 00:29:50,380
Huirou isn’t my biological daughter.

517
00:29:51,060 --> 00:29:52,140
But I treat her as one.

518
00:29:52,980 --> 00:29:54,620
She’s the apple of my eye.

519
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:57,260
I only want her

520
00:29:58,540 --> 00:30:01,900
to be a little girl all her life,

521
00:30:02,940 --> 00:30:04,460
who is always innocent and wayward.

522
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:10,700
When she understands what the teacher says,

523
00:30:11,820 --> 00:30:15,180
she’ll get tougher

524
00:30:17,420 --> 00:30:18,180
and stubborn.

525
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:26,700
You shall make decision

526
00:30:27,740 --> 00:30:28,940
on Huirou’s private affairs.

527
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:05,620
For my father, I built the Hall of Articles,

528
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:08,820
to save his manuscripts and books,

529
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,060
in the memory of him.

530
00:31:12,660 --> 00:31:15,860
Today, I burn incense and pray

531
00:31:16,340 --> 00:31:17,500
in the Hall of Articles,

532
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:19,740
just let my ancestors know

533
00:31:19,820 --> 00:31:21,300
what we’re going to discuss about.

534
00:31:22,340 --> 00:31:23,260
Sorry, ancestors.

535
00:31:24,220 --> 00:31:26,220
The system you made used to be perfect.

536
00:31:27,060 --> 00:31:29,940
But it eroded as time went by.

537
00:31:30,700 --> 00:31:33,140
Today, I’m going to develop new social laws

538
00:31:33,380 --> 00:31:36,020
with the Cabinet and Privy Council.

539
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:50,020
In 1028 A.D., Mr. Fan submitted a long report,

540
00:31:50,620 --> 00:31:51,860
proposing to reform officials’ management,

541
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:54,740
reduce officials and pacify generals.

542
00:31:55,860 --> 00:31:57,620
I wasn’t in power at that time,

543
00:31:58,340 --> 00:31:59,420
but I totally agreed with him.

544
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:01,780
Fifteen years have passed.

545
00:32:02,540 --> 00:32:04,220
Finally, I asked Mr. Fan to talk freely about

546
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:07,940
contemporary problems in front of the late Emperor.

547
00:32:09,820 --> 00:32:11,700
Huaiji, get the ink for Mr. Fan.

548
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:18,380
You flatter me, Your Majesty.

549
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:21,700
You’re a real scholar.

550
00:32:22,260 --> 00:32:25,220
I’m just respecting you the way it should be.

551
00:32:31,340 --> 00:32:32,940
Today, I opened the Hall of Articles

552
00:32:33,140 --> 00:32:34,660
and discussed with the Cabinet and Privy Council.

553
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:38,300
Among ten reform terms Fan Zhongyan proposed,

554
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:39,980
officials still want to

555
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:42,940
discuss about the military system again

556
00:32:42,940 --> 00:32:43,820
because it’s against the ancestral rule.

557
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:46,620
I’ll write down the rest terms

558
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:48,740
and announce them in two days,

559
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:49,900
for further implementation.

560
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:53,860
It starts from officials and imperial exams.

561
00:32:55,420 --> 00:32:56,220
Look, Danshu.

562
00:32:58,380 --> 00:33:00,900
In current schools, there are wise teachers

563
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:03,660
who can teach six classics

564
00:33:03,820 --> 00:33:05,500
and also the way of managing a country or people.

565
00:33:06,060 --> 00:33:08,780
But we only recruit scholars by narrating

566
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:10,380
and judge them by written articles.

567
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:13,500
People adopt literature instead of correct ways.

568
00:33:16,740 --> 00:33:17,900
Not only in current schools

569
00:33:18,300 --> 00:33:19,100
can teachers teach

570
00:33:19,100 --> 00:33:21,060
the way of managing a country or people.

571
00:33:22,060 --> 00:33:24,020
I still remember

572
00:33:24,380 --> 00:33:25,860
when I went to Nanjing Academy for classes

573
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:27,340
in the name of my brother,

574
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:30,660
teachers often taught us to write for truth.

575
00:33:31,260 --> 00:33:32,780
A vacuous article

576
00:33:32,940 --> 00:33:34,380
can never be good,

577
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:36,620
however many ornate phrases

578
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:37,980
or matching words it uses.

579
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:39,580
Not to mention

580
00:33:39,580 --> 00:33:40,460
those articles

581
00:33:40,460 --> 00:33:41,860
in deliberate pursuit of uncommon allusions.

582
00:33:44,140 --> 00:33:46,220
Do you know why?

583
00:33:48,620 --> 00:33:49,380
What?

584
00:33:50,940 --> 00:33:52,780
Why do we still recruit scholars

585
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:55,180
with written articles,

586
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:57,820
while official schools in different cities

587
00:33:57,820 --> 00:33:58,860
have already changed?

588
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:14,340
What’s this?

589
00:34:15,540 --> 00:34:16,820
A letter Mr. Yan wrote to me from Nanjing

590
00:34:17,740 --> 00:34:19,700
in 1027 A.D.

591
00:34:20,940 --> 00:34:23,860
By then, he was banished from the Capital

592
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,020
because he objected to the Empress Dowager

593
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,380
for using the government for private uses.

594
00:34:29,060 --> 00:34:30,460
I was only 17 years old

595
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:31,900
and I relied on Mr. Yan most.

596
00:34:32,060 --> 00:34:34,620
I was scared when he was leaving the Capital.

597
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:36,220
He told me

598
00:34:37,220 --> 00:34:38,780
he could do something in the Capital

599
00:34:39,100 --> 00:34:41,420
and do something else in another place.

600
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:59,060
The current standard for recruiting scholars...

601
00:35:05,340 --> 00:35:06,340
Don’t move. Don’t move.

602
00:35:10,940 --> 00:35:12,860
= The Fourth Princess Yaoyao =
You snatched my toy.

603
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,140
Here. Here. Here.

604
00:35:16,500 --> 00:35:17,460
Take this ball.

605
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:18,900
Come. Come over.

606
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:23,260
I like you.

607
00:35:25,700 --> 00:35:27,540
Look at you. You’ve got saliva.

608
00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:28,820
Wipe it.

609
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:34,820
Be careful. Be careful.

610
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:38,260
You walk so smoothly.

611
00:35:38,260 --> 00:35:40,020
Come. Why don’t you have a rest?

612
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:43,220
Still want to walk?

613
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:48,620
All right.

614
00:35:54,140 --> 00:35:55,300
Do you like this?

615
00:35:58,140 --> 00:36:00,580
Yaoyao? Yaoyao! Yaoyao!

616
00:36:00,580 --> 00:36:01,220
Yaoyao.

617
00:36:01,340 --> 00:36:02,140
What’s wrong?

618
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:04,940
Help! Anyone?

619
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:06,180
Anyone here?

620
00:36:07,300 --> 00:36:09,100
Somebody help! Anyone here?

621
00:36:09,660 --> 00:36:10,260
Princess...

622
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:10,820
What happened?

623
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:11,980
Princess... The Fourth Princess!

624
00:36:12,140 --> 00:36:13,260
She’s suffocated.

625
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:14,660
Take me there.

626
00:36:16,180 --> 00:36:17,500
Fan Zhongyan proposed that

627
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,740
students should take different classes

628
00:36:19,940 --> 00:36:21,020
based on their own skills.

629
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:23,540
They must apply what they have learned?

630
00:36:25,260 --> 00:36:27,500
That was exactly what I was thinking of.

631
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:29,860
That year, I wasn’t in power

632
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:31,460
and I couldn’t reform the imperial exam.

633
00:36:32,020 --> 00:36:32,980
But I could at least

634
00:36:32,980 --> 00:36:34,100
send wise officials

635
00:36:34,420 --> 00:36:35,300
like Mr. Yan

636
00:36:35,820 --> 00:36:37,020
to take charge of regional education

637
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:38,420
and change the teaching methods.

638
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:41,820
After a dozen years’ preparation,

639
00:36:42,260 --> 00:36:44,180
I can finally change

640
00:36:44,740 --> 00:36:46,700
the standard for imperial exams.

641
00:36:50,620 --> 00:36:51,660
That year,

642
00:36:52,820 --> 00:36:54,420
I managed to take lessons

643
00:36:54,660 --> 00:36:55,940
from famous teachers

644
00:36:56,620 --> 00:36:58,180
to broaden my horizon.

645
00:37:00,460 --> 00:37:02,340
So, it was your favor?

646
00:37:05,020 --> 00:37:06,580
Oh, what I did that year

647
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:08,820
not only nurtured some real scholars

648
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:10,020
such as Sun Fu and Shi Jie,

649
00:37:10,820 --> 00:37:12,060
but also prepared a wise wife

650
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:14,300
for me.

651
00:37:16,340 --> 00:37:18,020
Your Highness. Your Highness.

652
00:37:19,860 --> 00:37:20,660
Huirou?

653
00:37:22,380 --> 00:37:23,140
Your Highness.

654
00:37:23,940 --> 00:37:24,820
What’s up?

655
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:27,900
Mother told me

656
00:37:28,020 --> 00:37:29,860
you didn’t allow me to go to the Imperial School.

657
00:37:30,300 --> 00:37:32,060
She must be lying, isn’t she?

658
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:40,900
But why, Your Highness?

659
00:37:41,780 --> 00:37:42,620
Because...

660
00:37:43,020 --> 00:37:44,420
you’ve grown up.

661
00:37:45,300 --> 00:37:47,540
In the Imperial School, you take classes

662
00:37:47,580 --> 00:37:48,900
with young boys.

663
00:37:49,340 --> 00:37:50,540
You’re relatives from the clan,

664
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:52,140
but it’s somewhat inappropriate.

665
00:37:53,220 --> 00:37:55,340
And you’re turning eight soon.

666
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:57,900
Time to learn some needlework.

667
00:37:58,700 --> 00:38:01,740
But when you and father

668
00:38:01,900 --> 00:38:04,140
asked me to copy The Analects of Confucius,

669
00:38:04,180 --> 00:38:05,780
recite poems and retell The Commentary of Zuo,

670
00:38:06,220 --> 00:38:08,020
you said I wasn’t an ordinary girl.

671
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:09,420
As the eldest daughter of my father

672
00:38:09,620 --> 00:38:10,900
and the princess of our nation,

673
00:38:11,300 --> 00:38:12,940
I should learn from famous teachers

674
00:38:13,180 --> 00:38:14,980
to broaden my horizon and be more generous.

675
00:38:15,100 --> 00:38:16,500
So, I must study.

676
00:38:18,420 --> 00:38:20,020
I will ask the Imperial Recorder

677
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:21,460
to give you lectures

678
00:38:21,780 --> 00:38:23,180
in the Pavilion of Phoenix every day.

679
00:38:23,820 --> 00:38:24,700
Your Highness.

680
00:38:25,220 --> 00:38:27,540
Is the Imperial Recorder

681
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:30,860
as knowledgeable as Mr. Sun, Mr. Song or Mr. Shi

682
00:38:30,860 --> 00:38:32,180
in the Imperial School?

683
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:34,580
Certainly not.

684
00:38:35,460 --> 00:38:37,580
But he’s knowledgeable enough to teach you.

685
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:41,940
Then why did you study in Nanjing Academy

686
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:44,020
in someone else’s name?

687
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:51,140
Huirou.

688
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:54,660
When I was at your age,

689
00:38:55,140 --> 00:38:58,140
I reeled off The Book of Songs
and The Analects of Confucius.

690
00:38:59,060 --> 00:39:00,500
In my family, no other brother

691
00:39:00,540 --> 00:39:01,740
could be my equal.

692
00:39:03,460 --> 00:39:04,460
But tell me, Huirou.

693
00:39:04,820 --> 00:39:05,740
In the Imperial School,

694
00:39:06,140 --> 00:39:08,100
how many times have you done your homework?

695
00:39:08,300 --> 00:39:09,660
And when did you manage to answer questions

696
00:39:09,820 --> 00:39:11,300
in class?

697
00:39:17,940 --> 00:39:18,740
Huirou.

698
00:39:19,460 --> 00:39:21,020
You don’t like to recite poems,

699
00:39:21,180 --> 00:39:22,300
do you?

700
00:39:22,540 --> 00:39:24,060
You even complained to me.

701
00:39:25,380 --> 00:39:26,620
I was too young to understand.

702
00:39:26,860 --> 00:39:28,580
But now I like reciting poems.

703
00:39:32,660 --> 00:39:33,780
What do you like then?

704
00:39:34,660 --> 00:39:36,140
Why don’t you explain to me

705
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:38,180
the text Mr. Shi just taught you the other day?

706
00:39:39,540 --> 00:39:40,900
And then tell me

707
00:39:41,220 --> 00:39:42,420
why you like it.

708
00:39:53,380 --> 00:39:55,500
Father. Your Highness.

709
00:39:55,700 --> 00:39:57,220
I’m too stupid

710
00:39:57,900 --> 00:39:59,140
to study in the Imperial School

711
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:00,820
with my brothers.

712
00:40:01,580 --> 00:40:02,660
I’m going back to do needlework

713
00:40:03,020 --> 00:40:06,260
in the Pavilion of Phoenix every day.

714
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:48,020
♪ Isolated kite ♪

715
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:51,100
♪ Left everything behind ♪

716
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:54,420
♪ Lost soul ♪

717
00:40:54,420 --> 00:40:57,540
♪ Can’t feel cause he can’t love ♪

718
00:40:57,540 --> 00:41:00,660
♪ Fondness is a beam of light ♪

719
00:41:00,660 --> 00:41:03,780
♪ Shines in the dark ♪

720
00:41:03,820 --> 00:41:06,860
♪ That overshines stars ♪

721
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:13,740
♪ And nourishes all living things ♪

722
00:41:14,460 --> 00:41:17,180
♪ Those who love more are always hurt
by who love less ♪

723
00:41:17,180 --> 00:41:21,180
♪ I don’t want to remember, but I can’t forget ♪

724
00:41:21,180 --> 00:41:27,220
♪ My hair turns grey too soon
Laughing at me for being so sentimental ♪

725
00:41:27,220 --> 00:41:29,900
♪ Those who love more are always hurt
by who love less ♪

726
00:41:29,900 --> 00:41:33,820
♪ I love you so much, and hope you are well ♪

727
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:40,220
♪ Towards the direction of light ♪

728
00:41:40,220 --> 00:41:46,420
♪ Light it up for the people ♪

729
00:41:46,420 --> 00:41:52,580
♪ Cure the heartless injury ♪

730
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:08,540
♪ Those who love more are always hurt
by who love less ♪

731
00:42:08,540 --> 00:42:11,700
♪ I love you so much, and hope you are well ♪

732
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:14,860
♪ When and where are we now ♪

733
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:18,020
♪ I’m left alone, sobbing ♪

734
00:42:18,020 --> 00:42:21,060
♪ I love you so deeply that left
everything behind ♪

735
00:42:21,060 --> 00:42:23,500
♪ Life is always filled
with the sadness of parting ♪

736
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:27,420
♪ Forget the past and revenge with a smile,
leave all the obsession behind ♪

737
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:30,660
♪ We look at each other without words ♪

738
00:42:30,660 --> 00:42:33,460
♪ Drinking wine with pent-up sadness and love ♪

739
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:36,900
♪ Those who love more are always
hurt by who love less ♪

740
00:42:36,900 --> 00:42:40,140
♪ I love you so much, and hope you are well ♪

741
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:43,300
♪ When and where are we now ♪

742
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:46,500
♪ I’m left alone, sobbing ♪

743
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:52,740
♪ I love you so deeply that left everything behind ♪

744
00:42:52,740 --> 00:42:57,500
♪ How can I forget ♪
